@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

 INTRODUCTION


 Through using DelfInit instead of ListMod or Delfmem in the user-startup you 
 can safely activate Delfina and/or gain information about your Delfina setup.

 In addition DelfInit can be used as a work-a-round for "AHI killer" bug which
 appears with DelfMPEG and DelfAIFF programs, and for "initialization" bug
 which appears in 68040/68060 Amigas equipped with delfina library version
 4.13 or earlier.
@endnode

@node "Features" "Features"

 FEATURES


 · fast and safe Delfina initialization
 · usable with 020/030/040/060 CPUs
 · Delfina soundcard hardware query
 · work-a-rounds for "AHI killer" and "initialization" bugs
 · three patch modes: no patch, patch delfina library's initialization
   procedure (default mode), or patch all library functions
@endnode

