@node "Installation" "Installation"

 INSTALLATION


 @{b}Requirements@{ub}
 
  · about 34 kB of free disk space
  · @{"Installer version 43.3" link "Requirements" 37}

 @{b}How to install DelfInit on hard disk?@{ub}

 Just double-click the "Asenna_DelfInit" (for Finnish speaking) or 
 "Install_DelfInit" (for English speaking) icon and follow the given 
 instructions.

 Software consists of two components: binary executable (DelfInit command) 
 and documentation (DelfInit.guide and it's icon). Installer script will 
 copy those components into a selected target directory by your choice.

 @{b}How to test DelfInit without installing it?@{ub}

 Just double-click "Preview" icon. This script will execute the DelfInit 
 command and thus initialize your Delfina soundcard.

 @{b}How to automatize Delfina initialization?@{ub}

 I recommend modifying the user-startup file (located in S: device) after the 
 software installation in order to get DelfInit automatically executed each 
 time you boot your Amiga.

 Search for lines ";BEGIN Delfina" and ";END Delfina" and replace the 
 Delfmem or ListMod command (placed between these two lines) with DelfInit.

 @{b}How to uninstall DelfInit?@{ub}

 Currently there is no uninstallation script. In order to remove DelfInit and 
 its documentation, you have to locate DelfInit command, DelfInit.guide, and 
 DelfInit.guide.info and delete them manually. If you have modified 
 user-startup file for automatic Delfina initialization, remember to remove 
 DelfInit command from user-startup.
@endnode

@node "Running" "Running DelfInit"

 RUNNING DELFINIT


 @{b}Running from Workbench@{ub}

 DelfInit is a CLI program only.

 @{b}Running from CLI@{ub}

 Open a CLI/Shell window, type DelfInit, and press enter. You may hear a sharp
 "click" sound or not (depends on your configuration), and information about
 your Delfina soundcard will be printed on the shell window. If DelfInit does
 not jam or return any error messages, your soundcard has been successfully
 initialized.

 DelfInit accepts also @{"arguments" link "CLIarguments" 0} with which you can effect the initialization
 process.
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"

 USAGE


 @{b}Running@{ub}

 @{" Running DelfInit from Workbench    " link "Running" 5}
 @{" Running DelfInit from command line " link "Running" 9}

 @{b}Working with DelfInit@{ub}

 DelfInit initializes and shows information about your Delfina soundcard. In
 addition it can be used as a work-a-round for "initialization" and/or "AHI
 killer" bugs.

 Initialization:

 DelfInit initializes Delfina soundcard by opening the delfina library.
 Opening triggers library's own initialization procedure which prepares
 Delfina for use.

 Avoiding "initialization" bug:

 Sometimes delfina library's initialization procedure fails, causing Amiga to
 freeze. DelfInit fixes this "initialization" bug by modifying 68040/68060 CPU
 cache settings before opening the delfina library and by restoring the
 original settings when the library has finished the initialization.

 Avoiding "AHI killer" bug:

 This freezing bug appears when you quit DelfMPEG and execute DelfAIFF. It
 can be avoided by executing DelfInit before DelfAIFF. DelfInit fixes the bug
 by closing the delfina library and flushing it from memory and by opening it
 again. In order to work, there should not be even one program using the
 delfina library when DelfInit is performing the operation.

 If you want to know how to effect the initialization process, see
 @{"Arguments" link "CLIarguments" 0}

 If you want to automatize Delfina initialization, see
 @{"How to automatize Delfina initialization?" link "Installation" 25}
@endnode

@node "CLIarguments" "CLI arguments"

 CLI ARGUMENTS


 DelfInit NOPATCH/S,STICKY/S,QUIET/S

 If no arguments are supplied, DelfInit installs a temporary patch in order to
 by-pass delfina library's initialization bug and performs a fast query at the
 end of the initialization process in order to obtain and show information
 about your Delfina soundcard.

 You can change the default behaviour by using the following arguments:

   NOPATCH/S
     This switch will disable delfina library's temporary patching. Use it
     if you have delfina library version 4.14 or later.

   STICKY/S
     Activate run-time patch. This patch will propably have no effect on
     delfina library or the soundcard itself, but it will have effect on your
     Amiga's performance. However, it can be used as a last resource when
     nothing seems to make the soundcard work.

   QUIET/S
     Disable Delfina hardware query.
@endnode

@node "Preferences" "Preferences"

 PREFERENCES


 DelfInit does not need or use any preference file.
@endnode

@node "FAQ" "DelfInit FAQ"

 FAQ


 Q: Can I use DelfInit even if I do not have any problems with my Delfina?
 A: Yes you can. It is build primary for that purpose.

 Q: Does DelfInit fix delfina library's "initialization" bug?
 A: Yes it does.
    The bug appears only in Amigas equipped with 68040 or 68060 CPU while 
    using delfina library version 4.13 or earlier. The usual symptom of the 
    "initialization" bug is a random freeze effect on startup.
    When you execute DelfInit without NOPATCH switch, the bug will be fixed.

 Q: Does DelfInit fix the "AHI killer" bug?
 A: Yes and no. DelfInit can be used as a work-a-round.
    "AHI killer" bug appears when you use DelfAIFF just after DelfMPEG, in the
    case of delfina library version 4.15 or earlier. The cure to this bug is
    simple. When you have finished using DelfMPEG, execute DelfInit. After
    that you can start DelfAIFF without crashing your Amiga.

 Q: Does DelfInit fix Delfina's "fake crash" bug?
 A: No, but it might have a positive influence on the crashing frequency. I
    have received reports claiming that DelfInit reduces the amount of fake
    crashes.

 Q: How can I avoid Delfina's "fake crashes"?
 A: By updating your delfina library to the version 4.15.
    
 Q: Where can I get delfina library 4.15?
 A: From Petsoff when they release it.

 Q: Delfina still causes Amiga to freeze despite of DelfInit. What can I do?
 A: You have a hardware problem and DelfInit can not help you on that. But
    there is something you can do.

    Delfina Lite and Delfina Plus:

    · These Delfina models might suffer from timing problems (especially if
      you have a A1200 ZORRO card). Try inserting the Delfina card in a
      different ZORRO slot.
    · Before inserting Delfina in a ZORRO slot, check that the card and the
      slot are clean and there is no oxidizing. Clean them if necessary. Press
      the card firmly into the slot but not too hard, so that you do not
      damage the motherboard or the ZORRO card.
    · Claim for a replacement Delfina from Petsoff. According to Finnish laws
      they are obliged to supply a working replacement or give you your
      money back.
    · Update your Amiga 1200's motherboard.

 Q: Where can I find Delfinas' User Manuals?
 A: HTML versions of Delfina 1200 and Delfina Plus manuals can be found from
    Petsoff's web pages:

    http://www.petsoff.com/UserManual/Delfina1200.html
    http://www.petsoff.com/UserManual/DelfinaPlus.html

 Q: Are there instructions for installing DelfSer expansion module?
 A: DelfSer installation instructions are included in Delfina Plus User Manual.
@endnode

